data.enText: a feeling of being extremely tired, usually because of hard work or exercise

data.chText: 这个事故是驾驶员疲劳所致。
data.enText: Driver fatigue was to blame for the accident.

data.chText: 我快要累倒了，眼睛也睁不开了。
data.enText: I was dropping with fatigue and could not keep my eyes open.
a feeling of not wanting to do a particular activity any longer because you have done too much of it
weakness in metal or wood caused by repeated bending or stretching

data.chText: 机翼显示出金属疲劳的迹象。
data.enText: The wing of the plane showed signs of metal fatigue .

data.chText: 士兵杂役（尤指作为惩罚，如做打扫、帮厨）
data.enText: duties, such as cleaning and cooking, that soldiers have to do, especially as a punishment

word_means: 令人身心交瘁的；劳心劳力的
simple_means.memory_skill: fatig 疲倦 + ue → 疲劳

means: 令人身心交瘁的；劳心劳力的

tr: labor of a nonmilitary kind done by soldiers (cleaning or digging or draining or so on)
example: the soldiers were put on fatigue to teach them a lesson
they were assigned to kitchen fatigues

tr: (always used with a modifier) boredom resulting from overexposure to something
example: he was suffering from museum fatigue
after watching TV with her husband she had a bad case of football fatigue
the American public is experiencing scandal fatigue

tr: temporary loss of strength and energy resulting from hard physical or mental work
example: he was hospitalized for extreme fatigue
growing fatigue was apparent from the decline in the execution of their athletic skills
weariness overcame her after twelve hours and she fell asleep

tr: used of materials (especially metals) in a weakened state caused by long stress
exhaust or get tired through overuse or great strain or stress
example: We wore ourselves out on this hike

tr: lose interest or become bored with something or somebody
example: I'm so tired of your mother and her complaints about my food

value.def: Fatigue is a feeling of extreme physical or mental tiredness.

example.ex: She continued to have severe stomach cramps, aches, fatigue, and depression...
example.tran: 她仍然患有严重的胃痉挛，感觉疼痛、疲乏、抑郁。

example.ex: Clarke says his team could have lasted another 15 days before fatigue would have begun to take a toll.
example.tran: 克拉克说，他的团队本来还可以再坚持 15 天，只是疲劳可能会造成严重后果，只好作罢。

value.def: You can say that people are suffering from a particular kind of fatigue when they have been doing something for a long time and feel they can no longer continue to do it.

example.ex: ...compassion fatigue caused by endless TV and celebrity appeals.
example.tran: 没完没了的电视节目和名人呼吁而导致的同情心疲劳

example.ex: ...the result of four months of battle fatigue.
example.tran: 4 个月的战斗疲劳带来的后果

value.def: Fatigues are clothes that soldiers wear when they are fighting or when they are doing routine jobs.

example.ex: He never expected to return home wearing US combat fatigues.
example.tran: 他从没想到会穿着美国军服回家。

value.def: Fatigue in metal or wood is a weakness in it that is caused by repeated stress. Fatigue can cause the metal or wood to break.

example.ex: The problem turned out to be metal fatigue in the fuselage.
example.tran: 问题原来是飞机机身出现金属疲劳。

trans: 慢性疲劳综合征(常使用缩略形式 CFS)

partsOfSpeech.dec: fatig 疲倦 + ability 性质 → 易疲劳性
fatig 疲倦 + able 可…的，能…的；具有…性质的 → 易疲劳的
fatig 疲倦 + ue → 疲劳
fatigue 疲劳 + less 无…的，不…的 → 不会疲劳的，不知疲劳的
partsOfSpeech.d: 不会疲劳的，不知疲劳的

partsOfSpeech.dec: in 使… + de 否定 + fatig 疲倦 + able 可…的，能…的；具有…性质的 → 不知疲倦的
